techmeme.title: Epic Games announces that Fortnite is back on the App Store in the US for iPhone and iPad users, and on the Epic Games Store and AltStore in the EU (Chance Miller/9to5Mac)
Sweden passes a law criminalizing the purchase of live online sexual performances, including cam shows and sex chats; buying pre-recorded content remains legal (Charles Szumski/Euractiv)
Google rolls out Jules, its asynchronous, agentic coding assistant unveiled in December 2024, in public beta and expects to announce pricing after the beta (Emilia David/VentureBeat)
Palo Alto Networks reports Q3 revenue up 15% YoY to $2.29B, vs. $2.28B est., net income down 6% to $262.1M, and non-GAAP gross margin of 76%, vs. 77.2% est. (Jonathan Vanian/CNBC)
Take-Two plans to sell $1B of new stock to investors and use the proceeds for general corporate purposes, including repayment of debt and future acquisitions (Jason Schreier/Bloomberg)
